[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    556[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: S3 (per-consumer IAM scoping), S4 (HL7 v2 MLLP bridge security), S5 (Bedrock LLM-assisted interpretation BAA discipline), S6 (Transfer Family SFTP source-IP allowlist) are operational completeness findings.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Each is a domain-specific discipline that the recipe's mixed audience (executives, architects, engineers, PMs) benefits from being named explicitly even if engineers in healthcare integration teams already know them. S4 and S6 are both related to the on-premises-to-AWS PHI ingress surface, which is a domain-specific concern not covered well in any other recipe to date; if the editor pulls together a healthcare-integration-engineer appendix, S4 and S6 belong together.[K
