[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Customer-managed KMS keys for every PHI store with explicit framing of [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mscoring-results[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdecision-records[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprediction-outcome-pairs[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m as "highly inferential PHI" because they join patient identifiers with predicted treatment outcomes. The framing is correctly sharper than analytical-PHI: a row indicating "patient has a predicted 1.4 pp greater A1c reduction on GLP-1 versus SGLT2" implicitly reveals diabetes diagnosis, current treatment regimen, and the clinical inadequacy of current therapy. Briefing text in DynamoDB is explicitly named as PHI.[K
