[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    770[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    771[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mA model that predicts A1c well but cardiovascular outcomes poorly will pass calibration drift detection on the primary outcome and quietly produce inferior cardiovascular outcomes.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The 90-day cardiovascular event signal is rare but the cumulative pattern over thousands of patients is detectable; not matching the secondary outcome silences the signal.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    772[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    773[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe training-cohort-vs-surveillance-cohort comparison is asymmetric.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Training matches all outcomes; surveillance matches only the primary. The drift detection is therefore looking at one of several relevant signals and may declare stability when secondary-outcome drift is occurring.[K
