[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    369[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Lake Formation for column-level and row-level access control on the identity store's analytics surface.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Different audiences see different views. Treatment-context users see the current name with the prior-name display governed by the sensitivity classification. Operations users see the linkage but a constrained view of the prior names. Research users (for de-identified analytics) see the linked identity with no name detail at all. Lake Formation grants enforce the row-and-column distinctions; Athena query paths use the same grants. Same chapter pattern as 5.2, 5.3, 5.4, 5.5, 5.6.[K
