[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The PRIMARY defenses against scope drift are:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       1. The system prompt's SCOPE RULES (HARD) section.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       2. Bedrock Guardrails restricted-topic filters
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          (clinical_advice, financial_advice, legal_advice
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m           configured at minimum).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       3. The offline scope-drift review program (sampled
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          conversation review by clinical operations).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The keyword list here is intentionally small; production should
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rely on Bedrock Guardrails for runtime enforcement and on the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     review program for ongoing rule updates. This list is what
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     catches the model on its way out the door if the prompt and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the Guardrails both miss.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The function's behavior is correct; the documentation gap is what's worth flagging.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
